<title>Create a New Project Folder</title>
<section>
        <para>From JasperSoft Studio, open the menu File, select New and then Others....</para>
       	<figure>
			<title>Select New-&gt;Other</title>
			<screenshot>
				<mediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="11.png" format="PNG" contentwidth="800px" />
					</imageobject>
				</mediaobject>
			</screenshot>
		</figure>
        <para>
   			In the dialog that will appear type &quot;Jasper&quot; in the Wizards bar, this will filter all the actions showing only
        	the ones related to JasperSoft Studio, and from this filtered list select &quot;JasperReports Project&quot;. Then hit
       		Next.
        </para>
        <figure>
			<title>Select JasperReports Project</title>
			<screenshot>
				<mediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="12.png" format="PNG" contentwidth="800px" />
					</imageobject>
				</mediaobject>
			</screenshot>
		</figure>
        <para>At this point you need only to insert the name of the folder and hit Finish.</para>
        <figure>
			<title>Insert the Name of the Folder</title>
			<screenshot>
				<mediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="13.png" format="PNG" contentwidth="800px" />
					</imageobject>
				</mediaobject>
			</screenshot>
		</figure>
     	</section>
</section>
